Dates purse set for 1st PGA Tour event in S Korea  By Yoo Jee ho  SEOUL Oct 24 Yonhap The dates and the purse for the first PGA Tour event in South Korea have been set  Local conglomerate CJ Group on Monday held a signing ceremony with the PGA Tour to host the CJ Cup Nine Bridges The tournament will take place from Oct 19 to 22 2017 and will offer US 9 25 million in total purse money  This event will be part of the 2017 2018 PGA Tour season The country has previously held events sanctioned by the PGA Tour including last year s Presidents Cup but never a tour event  The field will feature 78 players  CJ and the PGA Tour are still trying to determine the venue and it will likely be either Nine Bridges on Jeju Island or Haesley Nine Bridges Golf Club in Yeoju Gyeonggi Province some 100 kilometers southeast of Seoul  According to a local organizer the two sides are also in talks over including at least 10 homegrown players in the event  The 2016 2017 season got under way with the Safeway Open earlier this month in California There will be 47 events and not counting the national championships of Britain and Canada there are only four non U S hosts Malaysia China Mexico and Puerto Rico  CJ will join the automobile giant Hyundai Motor as the Korean corporate sponsors on the tour Hyundai has been a title sponsor for the Hyundai Tournament of Champions since 2011 For 10 years starting in 2017 it will sponsor the Genesis Open in Los Angeles  jeeho yna co kr  END
