LEAD Dates purse set for 1st PGA Tour event in S Korea  ATTN ADDS details comments photo  By Yoo Jee ho  SEOUL Oct 24 Yonhap The dates and the purse for the first PGA Tour event in South Korea have been set  Local conglomerate CJ Group on Monday held a signing ceremony with the PGA Tour to host the CJ Cup Nine Bridges The tournament will take place from Oct 19 to 22 2017 and will offer US 9 25 million in total purse money  This event will be part of the 2017 2018 PGA Tour season The country has previously held events sanctioned by the PGA Tour including last year s Presidents Cup but never a tour event  The field will feature 78 players with the top 60 players coming from the FedEx Cup standings and the other spots filled by Korea PGA KPGA Tour players and others According to CJ the two sides are also in talks over including at least 10 homegrown players in the event  Sohn Kyung shik chairman of the CJ Group L and Jay Monahan deputy commissioner of the PGA Tour pose with their agreements after CJ signed on to host the CJ Cup Nine Bridges the first PGA Tour event in South Korea on Oct 24 2016 in Seoul Yonhap  CJ has agreed to a 10 year deal and will remain the host through 2026 The champion will receive 500 FedEx Cup points and a two year exemption on the tour  CJ and the PGA Tour are still trying to determine the venue and it will be either The Club at Nine Bridges on Jeju Island or Haesley Nine Bridges Golf Club in Yeoju Gyeonggi Province some 100 kilometers southeast of Seoul Both clubs are owned and operated by CJ  This commitment not only extends the reach of the PGA Tour said Jay Monahan deputy commissioner of the PGA Tour It also positions Korea as an integral part in the global sporting landscape  Monahan noted the passionate fan base for golf in South Korea as highlighted at last year s Presidents Cup in Incheon just west of Seoul and said the CJ Cup should also go a long way toward developing men s golf in the country  What s unique about this 10 year commitment is that it gives us an oppportunity to do something foundational in Korea Monahan added A few years from now we ll see more great Korean players at the very top of the game That s one of the core reasons why we re here  Sohn Kyung shik chairman of the CJ Group and the chief organizer of the tournament said he hopes the new event will provide the bridge for Korean prospects to realize their dreams  Over the next 10 years our group hopes to nurture young people s dreams Sohn said And this will also be the opportunity to promote the excellence of our country and our culture to the rest of the world  Kyeong Wook ho CJ s chief marketing officer said ensuring the consistent presence of Korean born players at the CJ Cup will also help grow the men s game  One of the key purposes of this event is to help young players realize their dreams Kyeong said We hope to make sure we ll have at least 10 Korean players in the field for all 10 years  The 2016 2017 season got underway with the Safeway Open earlier this month in California There will be 47 events and not counting the national championships of Britain and Canada there are only four non U S hosts Malaysia China Mexico and Puerto Rico  CJ will join the automobile giant Hyundai Motor as the Korean corporate sponsors on the tour Hyundai has been a title sponsor for the Hyundai Tournament of Champions since 2011 For 10 years starting in 2017 it will sponsor the Genesis Open in Los Angeles  jeeho yna co kr  END
