LEAD S Korea s financial regulators meet ASEAN ambassadors  ATTN UPDATES with remarks by Thai ambassador bank association s chief  SEOUL Oct 24 Yonhap South Korea s top financial regulators met with the ambassadors of Southeast Asian nations on Monday and requested support for banks here to launch businesses in their countries  Attracted by the infinite growth potential of ASEAN nations many South Korean banks with experience and capability are paying keen attention to tapping into the local market Yim Jong yong chairman of the Financial Services Commission FSC said during a dinner meeting with them at the Seoul building of the Korea Federation of Banks  He added South Korea and the ASEAN have become important partners to each other in various fields including economy security and culture  However he pointed out they face lots of difficulties due to differences in financial regulations and practices and limited access to local financial authorities  Yim asked the top envoys to be more active in helping resolve the issues  Zhin Woong seob governor of the Financial Supervisory Service FSS also said if South Korea s financial services will be of help to the economy of Southeast Asian nations including the creation of jobs  The heads of a dozen South Korean banks also joined the dinner session along with Ha Young koo chairman of the Korea Federation of Banks  South Korea s financial firms have a total of 111 branches in Southeast Asia after the first one opened in 1973  Ha stressed the importance of a finance diplomacy for closer cooperation in the financial sector between the two sides  In response Thai Ambassador to South Korea Sarun Charoensuwan who leads the ASEAN Committee in Seoul said South Korean banks will have more opportunities in Southeast Asian countries thanks to the recent launch of the ASEAN Economic Community an EU style economic bloc  lcd yna co kr  END
